#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:2
msgid "py.test 2.0.2: bug fixes, improved xfail/skip expressions, speed ups"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:4
msgid ""
"Welcome to pytest-2.0.2, a maintenance and bug fix release of pytest, a "
"mature testing tool for Python, supporting CPython 2.4-3.2, Jython and "
"latest PyPy interpreters.  See the extensive docs with tested examples here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:8
msgid "http://pytest.org/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:10
msgid "If you want to install or upgrade pytest, just type one of::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:12
msgid ""
"pip install -U pytest # or\n"
"easy_install -U pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:15
msgid ""
"Many thanks to all issue reporters and people asking questions or "
"complaining, particularly Jurko for his insistence, Laura, Victor and "
"Brianna for helping with improving and Ronny for his general advise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:20
msgid "best, holger krekel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:24
msgid "Changes between 2.0.1 and 2.0.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:26
msgid ""
"tackle issue32 - speed up test runs of very quick test functions by reducing "
"the relative overhead"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:29
msgid ""
"fix issue30 - extended xfail/skipif handling and improved reporting. If you "
"have a syntax error in your skip/xfail expressions you now get nice error "
"reports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:33
msgid ""
"Also you can now access module globals from xfail/skipif expressions so that "
"this for example works now::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:36
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"import mymodule\n"
"@pytest.mark.skipif(\"mymodule.__version__[0] == \"1\")\n"
"def test_function():\n"
"    pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:42
msgid ""
"This will not run the test function if the module's version string does not "
"start with a \"1\".  Note that specifying a string instead of a boolean "
"expressions allows py.test to report meaningful information when summarizing "
"a test run as to what conditions lead to skipping (or xfail-ing) tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:48
msgid ""
"fix issue28 - setup_method and pytest_generate_tests work together The "
"setup_method fixture method now gets called also for test function "
"invocations generated from the pytest_generate_tests hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:53
msgid ""
"fix issue27 - collectonly and keyword-selection (-k) now work together Also, "
"if you do \"py.test --collectonly -q\" you now get a flat list of test ids "
"that you can use to paste to the py.test commandline in order to execute a "
"particular test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:58
msgid ""
"fix issue25 avoid reported problems with --pdb and python3.2/encodings output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:60
msgid ""
"fix issue23 - tmpdir argument now works on Python3.2 and WindowsXP Starting "
"with Python3.2 os.symlink may be supported. By requiring a newer py lib "
"version the py.path.local() implementation acknowledges this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:65
msgid ""
"fixed typos in the docs (thanks Victor Garcia, Brianna Laugher) and "
"particular thanks to Laura Creighton who also reviewed parts of the "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:68
msgid ""
"fix slightly wrong output of verbose progress reporting for classes (thanks "
"Amaury)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:71
msgid ""
"more precise (avoiding of) deprecation warnings for node.Class|Function "
"accesses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/release-2.0.2.rst:73
msgid "avoid std unittest assertion helper code in tracebacks (thanks Ronny)"
msgstr ""
